Headquarters Regions: Washington DC Metro Area, East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: AFCEA Bethesda, a 501(c)(3) non-profit organization, encourages dialogue and partnership between the federal government and industry to solve today’s most critical IT challenges. Through widely attended programs, AFCEA Bethesda strives to foster better inter-agency communication, share best practices, identify mission-critical issues and management approaches, and increase engagement with industry IT solution and service providers. AFCEA Bethesda has enjoyed great success over the years in engaging the federal civilian space, making us the premier civilian chapter for AFCEA International. On average each year, they engage more than 250 primarily civilian, senior-government executives who participate as speakers and moderators for their annual events: Monthly Breakfast Series, IT Days, Technology Symposia, and Senior Government Executive Dinners. Their Chapter proceeds are donated entirely to academic scholarships. In addition, their annual A Night for the Children Gala has generated more than $7 million in proceeds for charities benefiting the health, welfare, and education of children. AFCEA Bethesda is the civilian-focused Chapter of AFCEA International. With more than 130 Chapters worldwide, AFCEA is a membership organization dedicated to increasing knowledge through the exploration of issues relevant to its members in information technology, communications and electronics for defense, homeland security and intelligence communities.

Description: Creative Learning on the Go (CLOTG) is a leading provider of tutoring services in the greater Central Florida area
Full Description: Creative Learning on the Go (CLOTG) is a leading provider of tutoring services in the greater Central Florida area, catering to children aged 3 to 15. Established over 5 years ago by Erica Young, CLOTG is built on the core principles of passion, hard work, dedication, and growth. At CLOTG, we believe in making educational development accessible to all, which is why our pricing is fair and transparent. Each child enrolled in our program receives a comprehensive package that includes all necessary resources and materials provided by our experienced instructors. All we ask in return is for your child to bring their willingness to learn and dedicate a minimum of 30 minutes per day to studying and reading at home. We firmly believe that preparation is the key to a child's educational future, and we strive to ensure they are fully prepared through our rigorous learning development program. CLOTG offers both face-to-face and virtual tutoring options to cater to the diverse needs of our learners. We understand that every child is unique, and our personalized approach ensures that each student receives the attention and guidance they need to thrive academically. Our services encompass a wide range of benefits included in the price. Each student is provided with a personalized binder, complete with materials and supplies essential for their learning journey. Additionally, we offer online study materials and pre- and post-testing diagnostic assessments to track progress and identify areas of improvement. Our team consists of a dedicated group of educators and student interns based in Central Florida, bringing together a wealth of experience in working with children, technology, and parents. What sets us apart is our nurturing, passionate, and flexible approach to education. We believe in creating an impactful learning experience for our students, and our team dedicates their hearts and time to ensure the best possible educational outcomes. Whether it's one-on-one tutoring, group sessions, or virtual support, CLOTG is committed to empowering young minds and setting them up for lifelong success. Join us on this exciting educational journey and discover the joy of learning with Creative Learning on the Go.
